There has always been an intimate conversation between time and space. The course of the planets, the moon phases, the alignment of stars hanging in the sky like a gigantic clock. Les Cabinotiers, our department dedicated to Grand Complication models has decided this year to pay tribute to the astronomical origins of time measurement with a collection called “ le Temps Céleste”.

#VacheronConstantin
#WatchesAndWonders2021

node.text:
Métiers d’Art Tribute to great explorers: a new window on the world and on history, opened by talented Master artisans

Bartolomeu Dias, Vasco da Gama, Pedro Álvares Cabral: Vacheron Constantin celebrates their spirit of adventure through a new series of three ten-piece limited editions, the Métiers d'Art Tribute to great explorers. Crafted in Grand Feu enamel, each dial depicts selected portions of a 1519 map from the Miller Atlas. These three masterpieces of miniaturisation and expertise are driven by the Manufacture 1120 AT movement. These new models, presented at Watches & Wonders 2021, are part of the theme of the Maison for 2021 : entitled Classic with a Twist, it highlights Vacheron Constantin’s creative energy, guided by an identity that celebrates a heritage and dares to deliver the unexpected.

#VacheronConstantin
#WatchesAndWonders2021

It is a prestigious circle where savvy collectors and keen insiders and enthusiasts relate to human values, knowledge transfer, master skills, innovation and scrupulous quality. 

Welcome to a House of Connoisseurs.

#OneOfNotMany
#VacheronConstantin

YIQING YIN 
Both inspired and inspiring, this talented young woman has made her recent entrance in the very close circle of Haute Couture creators. Born in China, Yiqing Yin has travelled the world and nourished her intuitive and innovative vision with many different influences. In total harmony with the spirit of the Égérie collection, her universe mixes poetry, pure elegance in a passionate quest for absolute beauty. 
Definitely One Of Not Many. 
Learn more: https://www.vacheron-constantin.com/en/manufacture/one-of-not-many.html

node.text:
⁣Vintage vibes on the wrist.⠀
⠀⠀
⏳ The ⁣𝗛𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝗾𝘂𝗲𝘀 𝗧𝗿𝗶𝗽𝗹𝗲 𝗖𝗮𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗱𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗿 𝟭𝟵𝟰𝟮 model, made of steel, is inspired by reference 4240, of which the first executions in yellow gold, pink gold or steel were introduced in 1942. ⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀
🌟 In keeping with the original, this understated and elegant model drives the hours, minutes, small seconds at 6 o’clock, along with hand-type date and day and month by aperture. The calendar indications appear in a choice of burgundy or dark blue, on a two-tone silvered dial typical of the era.⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀
🔥 The 40 mm-diameter case crafted in the Vacheron Constantin style features a number of character traits typical of the era, such as the distinctive “triple gadroon” caseband bearing “claw-type” lugs. ⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀
⠀⠀
📷 Picture courtesy of @theminutemon ⠀
⠀
⠀
⠀
⁣#VacheronConstantin #OneOfNotMany #vacheron #thehourlounge #watches #watch #watchesofinstagram #horology #watchoftheday #instawatch #geneva #swissmade #swisswatch⠀

⁣⁣One watch. Two timezones. Unlimited possibilities. ✈⠀⠀
⠀⠀
🌍The Overseas dual time enables simultaneous reading of the two time zones in a glance. The easily adjustable dual time caliber is housed in a 41 mm-diameter stainless steel case water-resistant to 150 metres and featuring a design that highlights the Overseas signature features. ⠀⠀⠀
⠀
Discover our new summer watch straps in limited editions. Three new colors to apply a fresh, new look to your watch. Available only in boutique. ⠀
⠀

⁣Finest Elegance. 💫⠀
Behind its classical feeling and timeless lines, the Égérie collection shows many audacious features when it comes to details. ⠀⠀
⠀
⠀
The signature touch of the Égérie is a daring off-centered display, designed around two intertwined circles. The date or the moon-phase is part of a subtle diagonal line formed by the Vacheron Constantin logo and the crown audaciously placed at 1.30 o’clock. ⠀⠀
⠀
⠀

Discover the ⁣𝗣𝗮𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗺𝗼𝗻𝘆 𝗿𝗲𝘁𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗱𝗲 𝗱𝗮𝘆-𝗱𝗮𝘁𝗲.⠀

⠀⠀
A round stepped case, slim bezel and fluted caseback; a railway-track minute circle, “bâtons de Genève” applied hour-markers and Dauphine-type hands: this elegant Traditionnelle Manual-Winding model combines the signature characteristics of the Traditionnelle collection.⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text:
⁣Out of this world. ⁣🪐⠀
⠀
⁣🌠 Based on a new grand complication movement that took us four years to develop, the Armillary tourbillon perpetual calendar- Planetaria takes orological virtuosity to a level rarely reached. With its 745 components, the timepiece regulated by a double-axis tourbillon stages some spectacular astronomical complications.⠀
⠀
⁣🌍 The two symmetrical rotating globes on the dial offer a three-dimensional representation of the two hemispheres providing a day and night indication everywhere in the world.⠀
⠀
⁣🗓️ Another unexpected feature brought to this model by our creative craftsmen lies in the retrograde display of its perpetual calendar.⠀
⠀
⁣🌌 Framed by a pink gold case, every detail the dial comes to magnify the great orchestration of time in a timepiece as spectacular visually than it is technically.⠀
⠀
⠀

A matter of ⁣𝙨𝙝𝙖𝙥𝙚. ⠀
⠀
💫 More than just a watch, it is a symbol, an emblematic expression of Vacheron Constantin's creativity. ⠀
⠀
⌛ Introduced exactly a century ago, the American 1921 model is one of the most outstanding landmarks in the heritage of the Manufacture, which celebrates its avant-garde spirit through three new variations dedicated to vintage watch collectors and connoisseurs. ⠀
⠀
A cushion-type case, the diagonal display, the crown positioned between 1 and 2 o’clock are all visual twists testifying to an aesthetic that appeals as much by its offset design as its timeless nature.⠀
⠀
